data.title: Ukraine war and impact on Med security: A conversation with Federica Mogherini
data.meta_description: The German Marshall Fund of the United States (GMF), a nonpartisan public policy think tank that focuses on relations between the US and Europe, hosts a conversation with Federica Mogherini, the European Union’s former foreign policy chief, on Russia’s ongoing war in Ukraine, developments in the Mediterranean region and the state of the transatlantic partnership.
data.text:
The German Marshall Fund of the United States (GMF), a nonpartisan public policy think tank that focuses on relations between the US and Europe, hosts a conversation with Federica Mogherini, the European Union’s former foreign policy chief, on Russia’s ongoing war in Ukraine, developments in the Mediterranean region and the state of the transatlantic partnership, in Brussels at 4 p.m. Central European Time (5 p.m. Greek time) on November 29. The discussion with Mogherini, now rector of the College of Europe in Bruges, will be moderated by GMF Vice President Ian Lesser.

Visit the GMF website for more information about the online event and register here.

The event will be livestreamed by ekathimerini.

Founded by Swiss-born American academic and philanthropist Guido Goldman (November 4, 1937 – November 30, 2020) in 1972 through a gift from Germany as a tribute to the Marshall Plan, GMF is headquartered in Washington, DC, with offices in Berlin, Brussels, Ankara, Belgrade, Bucharest, Paris and Warsaw.
